Privacy Policy
This Privacy Policy applies to the PositiveCooker app ("Application") for mobile devices, created by Elius Faustine ("Service Provider") as a free service. This service is intended for use "AS IS."

Information Collection and Use
The Application may collect information when you download, install, and use it. The information collected includes:

Device Information:

Your device's Internet Protocol (IP) address.
Operating system details.
Usage Data:

Pages visited within the Application.
Time and date of visits.
Duration of use for specific features.
Location Data:

The Application requests Bluetooth and location permissions to connect to your device and activate it. Location access is necessary for Bluetooth functionality and to scan QR codes for device setup and operation.

Camera Data:
Access to your device's camera is required solely to scan QR codes, enhancing user experience by enabling seamless device pairing and configuration.

How Information is Used
The Service Provider uses the collected information to:

Facilitate the primary functions of the Application, such as connecting to your device and scanning QR codes.
Improve the Application's performance and user experience.
Provide analytics to enhance features and services.
Anonymized and aggregated data may be shared with trusted third-party services for improvement and optimization purposes.

Third-Party Services
The Application may utilize third-party services with their own privacy policies. Below are links to the privacy policies of third-party service providers used in the Application:
Google Play Services   "https://policies.google.com/privacy"

Data Retention
The Service Provider will retain collected data as long as necessary to provide the service. 
Users may request data deletion by contacting the Service Provider at scopeelius@gmail.com.

Opt-Out Rights
You can stop all data collection by uninstalling the Application using the standard uninstall procedure for your device.

Children's Privacy
The Application is not intended for children under 13. The Service Provider does not knowingly collect data from children under this age. If you believe that a child has provided personal information, please contact the Service Provider to have the data removed.

Security
The Service Provider prioritizes safeguarding user information through physical, electronic, and procedural measures.

Changes to this Privacy Policy
This Privacy Policy may be updated periodically. Continued use of the Application indicates acceptance of any changes. Updates will be reflected on this page, with the effective date noted.

Effective Date: January 3, 2025

Contact Us
If you have questions about this Privacy Policy or the Application, please contact the Service Provider at:
scopeelius@gmail.com
